This paper is about generating adversarial samples for neural machine translation systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and discusses the efficacy of neural-based systems, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper could be relevant to neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) since it involves generating and analyzing data samples.
